## What this does

**Three side-by-side animated panels** running simultaneously on identical data:
- 🐌 **Bubble Sort** — O(n²), watch it suffer
- 🚀 **Merge Sort** — O(n log n), divide and conquer
- ⚡ **Quick Sort** — O(n log n) average, in-place

**Features that make the gap painful:**
| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Live step counters** | Comparisons, swaps/writes, total steps update in real-time |
| **Color coding** | Yellow = comparing, Red = swapping, Orange = pivot, Green = sorted |
| **Verdict banner** | Shows exact multiplier (e.g. "Merge Sort used **8.3× fewer steps**") |
| **Input types** | Random, Nearly Sorted, Reversed, Many Duplicates — try Reversed to make Bubble cry |
| **Speed control** | From ludicrous to turtle so you can watch the agony in detail |
| **Array size slider** | 20–120 elements — bigger = more humiliation for Bubble |

> **Pro tip:** Set input to **Reversed** + size to **120** + speed to **Fast** and watch Bubble Sort still be grinding away while the other two finished long ago.

